article.description: E Illinois beats Jacksonville St 59-50 in OT
article.headline: E Illinois beats Jacksonville St 59-50 in OT
article.linkText: E Illinois beats Jacksonville St 59-50 in OT
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Chris Olivier scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to help Eastern Illinois beat Jacksonville State 59-50 in overtime on Saturday. Eastern Illinois (8-6, 2-0 Ohio Valley) scored just 17 points before the break -- its lowest scoring half of the season -- and trailed by 12 after Jacksonville State's Avery Moore hit a 3-pointer with 7:52 left in regulation. Reggie Smith's steal and dunk sparked a 12-0 run, including five points apiece by Olivier and LeTrell Viser, which tied it at 40 about four minutes later. Eastern Illinois' Josh Piper made a layup with 21 seconds left made it 46-all and, after Jacksonville State (7-9) missed a layup with 1 second to go, forced overtime. Olivier outscored the Gamecocks, who made just 1 of 9 field goals and 2 of 4 free throws, in overtime. Moore led Jacksonville State with 14 points. D.J. Felder added 10 points and a career-high 13 rebounds.
